"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fuo1665702692291.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fuo1665702692291.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fuo1665702692291.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fuo1665702692291\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__ueopen_402310\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the current Uniface environment handle that can be used to instantiate\n      services.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__topic_d119510e1_d119511e1_d119512e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__codeblock_ms3_qws_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long ueopen (UHACT* phEnv );</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__topic_d85137e1_d85138e1_d85139e1_d85140e1_d85141e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148640e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__parml_ebq_rws_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">phEnv</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Uniface environment handle. This handle can be used in subsequent calls to\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstnew</code>. After use, <var class=\"keyword varname\">phEnv</var> must be freed by\n                  calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>. (Output)</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__topic_d85142e1_d85143e1_d85144e1_d85145e1_d85146e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148640e89\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ueopen</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__2\">Error constant</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__3\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__1\">1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__2\">UINI_SUCCESS</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__3\">Success</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__2\">UINI_LOAD_ERROR</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__3\">The Uniface environment was not\n                        initialized.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__1\">-4</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__2\">UINI_ALLOC_ERROR</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"fuo1665702692291__table_d14834e1_d14835e1_d14836e1__entry__3\">The supplied pointer is zero.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__p_d119525e1_d119526e1_d119527e1\">We recommend that you use the mnemonic values rather than the numeric values. For example, you should test for UINI_SUCCESS rather than for 1. While this might make your code slightly harder to debug, it improves on readability and portability.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__topic_d85147e1_d85148e1_d85149e1_d85150e1_d85151e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148640e167\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__topic_d85152e1_d85153e1_d85154e1_d85155e1_d85156e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148640e179\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__p_d119537e1_d119538e1_d119539e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code> returns the handle to the current Uniface environment, which can\n            be used as input parameter for subsequent calls to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstnew</code>. Your\n            program is responsible for freeing this handle after use. By not doing so, you could\n            cause a memory leak, which might become an issue if you call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code>\n            repeatedly but do not free the handles. To free the environment handle, call\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__p_d119540e1_d119541e1_d119542e1\">This functions is primarily meant for C code that\n            is called by Uniface, and for C code that needs to call in to Uniface. In this case, the\n            environment has already been initialized by the Uniface application, so all you need to\n            do is to get a handle.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__p_d119543e1_d119544e1_d119545e1\">If you have created the Uniface environment\n            yourself by calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>, there is no need to call\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code>, because you can use the handle that was returned by\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>. Although there is no point in it, it is allowed to call\n            both <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code>. Note that generated call-in\n            stubs always start by calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">ueopen</code>, because they have no way of\n            knowing whether you have explicitly called <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__section_ygw_cxz_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148640e228\">Example</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following contrived example shows how C code can call in to Uniface\n            using the call-in API.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fuo1665702692291_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fuo1665702692291__codeblock_mrk_yws_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\nEXPORT void TESTCALLIN (void)\n{\nUHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */\nUHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */\nlong procErr; /* ProcScript error return parameter */\nlong opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */\nueopen(&amp;hEnv); /* Get the environment handle */\nuinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, /* Instantiate service MYSVC */\nUDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, &amp;procErr);\nuinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &amp;hOp); /* Instantiate EXEC operation */\nuopract (hOp, &amp;opStat, &amp;procErr); /* Activate the operation */\nuinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free the operation handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free the instance handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/its1665702691215.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uecreate</a><p>Initialize the Uniface runtime for component call-in.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qrb1665702691766.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufreeh</a><p>Free (delete) a handle.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iou1665702692361.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinstnew</a><p>Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527669\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ueopen Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return the current Uniface environment handle that can be used to instantiate services. long ueopen (UHACT* phEnv ); Copy Parameters phEnv Uniface environment handle. This handle can be used in subsequent calls to uinstnew . After use, phEnv must be freed by calling ufreeh . (Output) Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ueopen Value Error constant Meaning 1 UINI_SUCCESS Success -1 UINI_LOAD_ERROR The Uniface environment was not initialized. -4 UINI_ALLOC_ERROR The supplied pointer is zero. We recommend that you use the mnemonic values rather than the numeric values. For example, you should test for UINI_SUCCESS rather than for 1. While this might make your code slightly harder to debug, it improves on readability and portability. Use Library: ucall Description ueopen returns the handle to the current Uniface environment, which can be used as input parameter for subsequent calls to uinstnew . Your program is responsible for freeing this handle after use. By not doing so, you could cause a memory leak, which might become an issue if you call ueopen repeatedly but do not free the handles. To free the environment handle, call ufreeh . This functions is primarily meant for C code that is called by Uniface, and for C code that needs to call in to Uniface. In this case, the environment has already been initialized by the Uniface application, so all you need to do is to get a handle. If you have created the Uniface environment yourself by calling uecreate , there is no need to call ueopen , because you can use the handle that was returned by uecreate . Although there is no point in it, it is allowed to call both uecreate and ueopen . Note that generated call-in stubs always start by calling ueopen , because they have no way of knowing whether you have explicitly called uecreate . Example The following contrived example shows how C code can call in to Uniface using the call-in API. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> EXPORT void TESTCALLIN (void) { UHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */ UHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */ long procErr; /* ProcScript error return parameter */ long opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */ ueopen(&hEnv); /* Get the environment handle */ uinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, /* Instantiate service MYSVC */ UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, &procErr); uinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &hOp); /* Instantiate EXEC operation */ uopract (hOp, &opStat, &procErr); /* Activate the operation */ uinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free the operation handle */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free the instance handle */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */ } Copy Related Links uecreate Initialize the Uniface runtime for component call-in. ufreeh Free (delete) a handle. uinstnew Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}